channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: The CropAndWeed Dataset: A Multi-Modal Learning Approach for Efficient Crop and Weed Manipulation
item.description: Precision Agriculture and especially the application of automated weed intervention represents an increasingly essential research area, as sustainability and efficiency considerations are becoming more and more relevant.

item.title: FICE: Text-Conditioned Fashion Image Editing With Guided GAN Inversion
item.description: We address these constraints by proposing a novel text-conditioned editing model, called FICE (Fashion Image CLIP Editing), capable of handling a wide variety of diverse text descriptions to guide the editing procedure.

item.title: Towards Long-Term Time-Series Forecasting: Feature, Pattern, and Distribution
item.description: Long-term time-series forecasting (LTTF) has become a pressing demand in many applications, such as wind power supply planning.

item.title: Neural Codec Language Models are Zero-Shot Text to Speech Synthesizers

item.title: Instance-based Explanations for Gradient Boosting Machine Predictions with AXIL Weights
item.description: The weights used in these linear combinations are measures of instance importance, complementing existing measures of feature importance, such as SHAP and LIME.

item.title: All in Tokens: Unifying Output Space of Visual Tasks via Soft Token
item.description: With these new techniques and other designs, we show that the proposed general-purpose task-solver can perform both instance segmentation and depth estimation well.

item.title: Critical Perspectives: A Benchmark Revealing Pitfalls in PerspectiveAPI
item.description: Detecting "toxic" language in internet content is a pressing social and technical challenge.

item.title: Learning Goal-Conditioned Policies Offline with Self-Supervised Reward Shaping
item.description: Developing agents that can execute multiple skills by learning from pre-collected datasets is an important problem in robotics, where online interaction with the environment is extremely time-consuming.

item.title: CAT: LoCalization and IdentificAtion Cascade Detection Transformer for Open-World Object Detection
item.description: Open-world object detection (OWOD), as a more general and challenging goal, requires the model trained from data on known objects to detect both known and unknown objects and incrementally learn to identify these unknown objects.

item.title: Beyond spectral gap (extended): The role of the topology in decentralized learning
item.description: This paper aims to paint an accurate picture of sparsely-connected distributed optimization.

item.title: HyperReel: High-Fidelity 6-DoF Video with Ray-Conditioned Sampling
item.description: Volumetric scene representations enable photorealistic view synthesis for static scenes and form the basis of several existing 6-DoF video techniques.

item.title: Automatic Sound Event Detection and Classification of Great Ape Calls Using Neural Networks
item.description: We present a novel approach to automatically detect and classify great ape calls from continuous raw audio recordings collected during field research.

item.title: Towards Autoformalization of Mathematics and Code Correctness: Experiments with Elementary Proofs
item.description: The ever-growing complexity of mathematical proofs makes their manual verification by mathematicians very cognitively demanding.

item.title: Randomized Message-Interception Smoothing: Gray-box Certificates for Graph Neural Networks
item.description: To remedy this, we propose novel gray-box certificates that exploit the message-passing principle of GNNs: We randomly intercept messages and carefully analyze the probability that messages from adversarially controlled nodes reach their target nodes.

item.title: CiT: Curation in Training for Effective Vision-Language Data
item.description: Large vision-language models are generally applicable to many downstream tasks, but come at an exorbitant training cost that only large institutions can afford.

item.title: TextDescriptives: A Python package for calculating a large variety of statistics from text
item.description: TextDescriptives is a Python package for calculating a large variety of statistics from text.

item.title: Learning Feature Recovery Transformer for Occluded Person Re-identification
item.description: To reduce the interference of the noise during feature matching, we mainly focus on visible regions that appear in both images and develop a visibility graph to calculate the similarity.

item.title: Open-Set Face Identification on Few-Shot Gallery by Fine-Tuning
item.description: In this paper, we focus on addressing the open-set face identification problem on a few-shot gallery by fine-tuning.

item.title: ANNA: Abstractive Text-to-Image Synthesis with Filtered News Captions
item.description: Advancements in Text-to-Image synthesis over recent years have focused more on improving the quality of generated samples on datasets with descriptive captions.

item.title: Towards a Pipeline for Real-Time Visualization of Faces for VR-based Telepresence and Live Broadcasting Utilizing Neural Rendering
item.description: Compared to the long line of research in VR, reconstruction of faces hidden beneath an HMD is a very recent topic of research.

item.title: Iterated Decomposition: Improving Science Q&A by Supervising Reasoning Processes
item.description: We apply iterated decomposition to three real-world tasks and improve the accuracy of LM programs over less compositional baselines: describing the placebo used in a randomized controlled trial (25% to 65%), evaluating participant adherence to a medical intervention (53% to 70%), and answering NLP questions on the Qasper dataset (38% to 69%).

item.title: On Fairness of Medical Image Classification with Multiple Sensitive Attributes via Learning Orthogonal Representations
item.description: In this paper, we propose a novel method for fair representation learning with respect to multi-sensitive attributes.

item.title: A general framework for implementing distances for categorical variables
item.description: For categorical data, the definition of a distance is more complex, as there is no straightforward quantification of the size of the observed differences.

item.title: Emergent collective intelligence from massive-agent cooperation and competition
item.description: Since these learned group strategies arise from individual decisions without an explicit coordination mechanism, we claim that artificial collective intelligence emerges from massive-agent cooperation and competition.

item.title: PENDANTSS: PEnalized Norm-ratios Disentangling Additive Noise, Trend and Sparse Spikes
item.description: Denoising, detrending, deconvolution: usual restoration tasks, traditionally decoupled.

item.title: Audio-Visual Efficient Conformer for Robust Speech Recognition
item.description: We improve previous lip reading methods using an Efficient Conformer back-end on top of a ResNet-18 visual front-end and by adding intermediate CTC losses between blocks.

item.title: Multi-Aspect Explainable Inductive Relation Prediction by Sentence Transformer
item.description: Recent studies on knowledge graphs (KGs) show that path-based methods empowered by pre-trained language models perform well in the provision of inductive and explainable relation predictions.

item.title: PACO: Parts and Attributes of Common Objects
item.description: This motivates the need for large datasets which go beyond traditional object masks and provide richer annotations such as part masks and attributes.

item.title: Robofriend: An Adpative Storytelling Robotic Teddy Bear - Technical Report
item.description: In this paper we describe Robofriend, a robotic teddy bear for telling stories to young children.

item.title: Federated Learning for Data Streams
item.description: Federated learning (FL) is an effective solution to train machine learning models on the increasing amount of data generated by IoT devices and smartphones while keeping such data localized.

item.title: Availability Adversarial Attack and Countermeasures for Deep Learning-based Load Forecasting
item.description: To tackle this attack, an adversarial training algorithm is proposed.

item.title: MoBYv2AL: Self-supervised Active Learning for Image Classification
item.description: We present MoBYv2AL, a novel self-supervised active learning framework for image classification.

item.title: Recursive classification of satellite imaging time-series: An application to water and land cover mapping
item.description: Our method also improves the performance of deep learning-based classifiers without the need of additional training data.

item.title: Motion-based Post-Processing: Using Kalman Filter to Exclude Similar Targets in Underwater Object Tracking
item.description: We improved SOTA trackers based on our method, and proved the effectiveness of our method on UOT100 and UTB180.

item.title: Fragment-based t-SMILES for de novo molecular generation
item.description: At present, sequence-based and graph-based models are two of popular used molecular generative models.

item.title: InPars-v2: Large Language Models as Efficient Dataset Generators for Information Retrieval
item.description: Recently, InPars introduced a method to efficiently use large language models (LLMs) in information retrieval tasks: via few-shot examples, an LLM is induced to generate relevant queries for documents.

item.title: Automatically Prepare Training Data for YOLO Using Robotic In-Hand Observation and Synthesis
item.description: The collected and synthetic images are combined to train a deep detection neural network.

item.title: UniHD at TSAR-2022 Shared Task: Is Compute All We Need for Lexical Simplification?
item.description: Previous state-of-the-art models for lexical simplification consist of complex pipelines with several components, each of which requires deep technical knowledge and fine-tuned interaction to achieve its full potential.

item.title: Modeling Sequential Recommendation as Missing Information Imputation
item.description: We propose a sequential recommendation model, called missing information imputation recommender (MIIR), that builds on the idea of MII and simultaneously imputes missing item feature values and predicts the next item.

item.title: Data-Driven Model Identification via Hyperparameter Optimization for the Autonomous Racing System
item.description: We utilize MIHO for the dynamics parameters of the AV-21, the full-scaled autonomous race vehicle, and integrate them into our model-based planning and control systems.

item.title: Extending Source Code Pre-Trained Language Models to Summarise Decompiled Binaries
item.description: While the automated summarisation of decompiled code can help Reverse Engineers understand and analyse binaries, current work mainly focuses on summarising source code, and no suitable dataset exists for this task.

item.title: SPTS v2: Single-Point Scene Text Spotting
item.description: End-to-end scene text spotting has made significant progress due to its intrinsic synergy between text detection and recognition.

item.title: Global excitability and network structure in the human brain
item.description: We utilize a model of Wilson-Cowan oscillators to investigate structure-function relationships in the human brain by means of simulations of the spontaneous dynamics of brain networks generated through human connectome data.

item.title: Large Language Models as Corporate Lobbyists
item.description: We use hundreds of ground-truth labels of the relevance of a bill to a company to benchmark the performance of the model, which outperforms the baseline of predicting the most common outcome of irrelevance.

item.title: MGTAB: A Multi-Relational Graph-Based Twitter Account Detection Benchmark
item.description: However, in addition to low annotation quality, existing benchmarks generally have incomplete user relationships, suppressing graph-based account detection research.

item.title: Cross Modal Transformer via Coordinates Encoding for 3D Object Dectection
item.description: In this paper, we propose a robust 3D detector, named Cross Modal Transformer (CMT), for end-to-end 3D multi-modal detection.

item.title: StyleTalk: One-shot Talking Head Generation with Controllable Speaking Styles
item.description: In a nutshell, we aim to attain a speaking style from an arbitrary reference speaking video and then drive the one-shot portrait to speak with the reference speaking style and another piece of audio.

item.title: Backdoor Attacks Against Dataset Distillation

item.title: KoopmanLab: A PyTorch module of Koopman neural operator family for solving partial differential equations
item.description: Here we present KoopmanLab, a self-contained and user-friendly PyTorch module of the Koopman neural operator family for solving partial differential equations.
